name: Villa Angel D'Uma
address: GJC8+M43, Jl. Raya Perasi, Subagan, Kec. Karangasem, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80813, Indonesia
review 1: The villa itself is nice. Has a space underneath which is shady and cool. I would highly recommend you engage the owner Made as a guide. There are lots of really unique experiences nearby and he can take you in a car with AC. Gave me an insight into  Balinese culture that I'll never forget.
review 2: An amazing villa, that we loved staying it. Beautifully maintained garden, comfy bed, and lots of nice places nearby. Rented scooter through them too. Very cheap for the space. Would definitely recommend.
review 3:
DO NOT GO - THEFT ALERT!
Some of my property was stolen at this villa, and the owner blamed me. I had left it outside (but in the house in the villa) and it was stolen during the night while I was sleeping, when you think about the fact that this villa is in the middle of nowhere, it is quite scary to think that someone would go all the way there while you're sleeping, really creepy.
review 5: In the middle of a rice field...thos villa has a beautiful private garden, 2 bedrooms which are a good size, only 1 with Aircon, but other has a fan...and another fan in the kitchen...large entertainment and chill area downstairs...nice kitchen and bathroom upstairs...attentive host Mr Made was appreciated...reminded me of old peaceful Bali

name: Warung Makan Lesehan Astiti Jaya
address: GJC8+X2H, Jl. Raya Perasi, Subagan, Kec. Karangasem, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80811, Indonesia
review 1:
Its a very traditional food, you wouldn't find menu, because its only serve one pack per person ( satay, soup with meatballs, vegetables, rice ) and all from fish.

The portion is big , the taste is good too,

If you want to order ala carte, just told the staff you want satay only or soup only in the front.
review 2: Spacious and comfortable restaurant. Excellent service. Pescatarian and vegan friendly. Family friendly. Delicious food ðŸ˜‹ nasi Ikan enak sekali!
review 3: Fish based nasi campur was truly tasty
review 4:
Great food, very tasty meat fish satay, fish soup, except the vegy was just horible. Seem like she keeps it in the friedge and serve it straight to you. It was ice cold ðŸ˜…. And the coco fish satay was very raw. I could not eat em. Busy warung. Only 3 of them work.
No price list or menu available on the table nor on the wall. I ve been there 3x. The lady who serves the food  always no smile. Even i try to talk to her. Well... seem like she is never happy to see customer.
Be ware when you pay your food. Its better to ask her the price of the food that you order. N calculate em yrself. Otherwise you will pay more than you should. Last time her calculator didnt work. ðŸ˜….
